FBIS3-34394 "drnes026_l_94007" FBIS-NES-94-026 Document Type:Daily Report 8 Feb 1994 ISRAEL Poll: Ramon Best for Premier After Rabin, Peres TA0402115494 Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT in Hebrew 4 Feb 94 p 1 TA0402115494 Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT Language: Hebrew Article Type:BFN ["Public opinion poll conducted for YEDI'OT AHARONOT by the Dahaf Institute directed by Dr. Mina Tzemah;" all results cited in percentages] [Excerpts] Question: If Yitzhaq Rabin and Shim'on Peres decide not to run in the next elections, which of the following Labor figures would be the most suitable for the post of prime minister? ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | |General public |Labor party supporters | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Binyamin Ben-Eli'ezer |12 |17 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Hayim Ramon |30 |31 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Avraham Shohat |5 |5 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Moshe Shahal |11 |11 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Did not reply |42 |36 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- [Passage omitted] The poll, which was conducted on 1 and 2 February from 512 interviewees constituting a representative sample of the adult Israeli population. The maximum margin of error is 4 percent.
